      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"quiet\" doesn't feel like a space for my voice. It just feels like a void. It’s like I’m a ghost haunting a house that was meant for two people. I look at his side of the bed and I just feel this crushing weight, like I'm carrying a mountain. Everything we built, everywhere we planned to go... it’s all just gone. I don't see the point in building anything new. What's even the point of trying to exist in a world where he isn't?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
